embeds.description: Here you can find the full command list for this bot.

fields.name: +ticket create | +new <subject>
fields.value: Create a new ticket.

fields.name: +ticket archive | +archive
fields.value: Archive an active ticket.

fields.name: +ticket add|remove <user mention or ID> | +add|remove <user mention or ID>
fields.value: Add or remove a user from a ticket.

fields.name: +ticket blacklist <list|add|remove> (<user mention or ID> [reason])
fields.value: Ban or unban a user from creating tickets in this server with an optional reason that will show if they try and create one. The 'list' option provides a list of all the blacklisted users in the guild. You do not need to provide a user or reason when using the 'list' command.

fields.name: +ticket creation <enable|disable> [reason]
fields.value: Enable or disable ticket creation for the whole server. If disabled, no new tickets can be created and an error message with the reason will be displayed.

fields.name: +ticket closeall
fields.value: Closes all open tickets. Running this command isn't recommended as there will be no ticket logs or closure messages sent out.

fields.name: +ticket setformat <new format>
fields.value: Sets the information format which is shown to users when they create a ticket.

fields.name: +ticket setprefix <new prefix>
fields.value: Set a new command prefix for this server.

fields.name: +ticket transcript
fields.value: Request the transcript link for the ticket which you used this command in.

fields.name: +ticket resetnumbering
fields.value: Resets the ticket numbering for this server; your next ticket created will be called 'ticket-1'.
